The British Government has been a leading supplier of weapons to the Ukrainian army ever since hostilities broke out in February. The UK has sent more than 5,000 anti-tank missiles, 1,360 anti-structure munitions, five air-defence systems with more than 100 missiles, and 4.5 tonnes of plastic explosives, according to the Ministry of Defence. Britain's unswerving support for Kyiv has infuriated Moscow and led to threats of retaliation by the Kremlin. On his Rossiya-1 talkshow, host Vladimir Solovyov floated the idea of an attack on the UK by Russia. He said: "What is preventing us from striking the territory of the United Kingdom, targeting those logistical centres where these arms are being loaded?‚Äù FOLLOW BELOW FOR LATEST UPDATES